ECOLOGY: The only known locality record occurs in deciduous forest at low elevation. The habitus is consistent with the fossorial, pelophilous ecomorphotype (
Prendini, 2001b
). The spe- cies probably excavates deep burrows in sandy-loam soil, in open ground.
